1
00:00:03,470 --> 00:00:07,007
Narrator: We are
no different from the ants.

2
00:00:08,141 --> 00:00:10,677
No, we are far worse.

3
00:00:10,711 --> 00:00:12,646
♪

4
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:38,605
( Gunshot )

5
00:01:27,354 --> 00:01:28,322
( No audible dialogue )

6
00:01:28,355 --> 00:01:29,456
( Glasses clink )

7
00:01:35,496 --> 00:01:38,332
The Rose had poisoned thorns.

8
00:01:38,365 --> 00:01:42,269
The poison which spread when
the Rose came into full bloom

9
00:01:42,302 --> 00:01:45,472
was stronger
than toxins similar in nature.

10
00:01:45,506 --> 00:01:47,575
Those killed instantly
in the blast

11
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:49,043
were the lucky ones.

12
00:01:49,076 --> 00:01:50,344
In survivors’s bodies,

13
00:01:50,377 --> 00:01:52,312
the poison was absorbed,

14
00:01:52,346 --> 00:01:55,149
eating them away
from the inside.

15
00:01:55,182 --> 00:01:58,719
The rapid destruction of
their organs began soon after,

16
00:01:58,752 --> 00:02:01,154
but this was
not the only effect.

17
00:02:01,188 --> 00:02:03,557
The poison also
turned them into carriers

18
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:07,127
who went on
to contaminate new victims.

19
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:10,797
The rate at which the poison
killed was exquisitely timed

20
00:02:10,831 --> 00:02:12,433
and allowed it to create

21
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:15,302
a chain reaction
of mass casualties.

22
00:02:16,403 --> 00:02:17,771
In other words...

23
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:20,307
( Shaiapouf gagging )

24
00:02:26,613 --> 00:02:30,150
Narrator: It was a weapon
expressly engineered

25
00:02:30,184 --> 00:02:32,787
to be the ultimate evil.

26
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:33,787
♪

27
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:35,755
( Singing in Japanese )

28
00:03:17,464 --> 00:03:19,399
( Whooshing )

29
00:03:24,872 --> 00:03:26,407
( Splashes echo )

30
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,375
♪

31
00:03:31,945 --> 00:03:34,681
Shaiapouf: Th-this is--

32
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:37,917
what is happening?

33
00:03:37,951 --> 00:03:39,686
What’s wrong with me?

34
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:45,892
Meruem: Pouf.

35
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:55,502
Shaiapouf:
Is something wrong, lord meruem?

36
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:05,379
Sire, I hope you’ve had
the chance to reconsider,

37
00:04:05,412 --> 00:04:08,916
and if you have,
then we must evacuate.

38
00:04:11,218 --> 00:04:12,786
Sire?

39
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:15,889
Meruem: He knows that I
can see right through him,

40
00:04:15,923 --> 00:04:19,427
yet he still refuses
to divulge his secret.

41
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:21,394
Very well.

42
00:04:21,428 --> 00:04:23,330
All that’s left to do

43
00:04:23,363 --> 00:04:27,400
is for me to locate and capture
all of the remaining intruders.

44
00:04:27,434 --> 00:04:29,870
Your secret intrigues me,

45
00:04:29,903 --> 00:04:32,606
and I intend to know it
soon enough.

46
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:34,908
You still intend to tell me,
don’t you?

47
00:04:34,942 --> 00:04:37,812
I would strongly advise
against changing your mind.

48
00:04:37,845 --> 00:04:39,780
♪

49
00:04:41,648 --> 00:04:43,850
Shaiapouf:
I will keep my word, sire,

50
00:04:43,884 --> 00:04:45,953
even if it costs me my life.

51
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:50,757
Meruem: Wise answer.

52
00:05:01,502 --> 00:05:02,837
♪

53
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:04,705
Shaiapouf: He’s already using

54
00:05:04,738 --> 00:05:06,940
the final en search
that he’s permitted.

55
00:05:10,344 --> 00:05:14,381
Meruem: I can see everything.

56
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:18,451
I can see all that has changed
since the first time I used en--

57
00:05:18,485 --> 00:05:22,456
footprints
that weren’t there before,

58
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:25,258
an abandoned vehicle...

59
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:28,829
Youpi’s corpse...

60
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:33,266
A door that’s been opened...

61
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:37,004
And someone new
who reacts to my en.

62
00:05:40,908 --> 00:05:43,411
( Welfin gasps )

63
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:47,814
( Heart beating )

64
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,288
Meruem:
Someone has killed youpi.

65
00:05:55,322 --> 00:05:56,490
Was it you?

66
00:05:56,523 --> 00:05:58,291
( Welfin gasps )

67
00:05:58,325 --> 00:06:01,695
No, sire. Absolutely not.

68
00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:03,763
I’m just
a lowly squadron leader.

69
00:06:03,797 --> 00:06:07,000
I respected sir youpi,
and I had no reason to kill him.

70
00:06:07,034 --> 00:06:08,402
( Swallows )

71
00:06:08,435 --> 00:06:10,070
We were just talking,

72
00:06:10,103 --> 00:06:13,640
a-and then suddenly
sir youpi coughed up blood,

73
00:06:13,674 --> 00:06:15,910
doubled over in pain.
Then he died.

74
00:06:15,943 --> 00:06:17,611
That’s all that happened!

75
00:06:17,644 --> 00:06:19,779
You’ve just gotta
believe me, sire!

76
00:06:19,813 --> 00:06:21,515
I’m not lying.

77
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:24,851
I mean, sure,
I did shoot youpi...

78
00:06:28,755 --> 00:06:33,593
But then, before he could
even answer my question,

79
00:06:33,627 --> 00:06:38,098
before my black centipedes
even had a chance to hatch,

80
00:06:38,131 --> 00:06:39,666
he was dead.

81
00:06:41,034 --> 00:06:43,970
I think,
before sir youpi ran into me,

82
00:06:44,004 --> 00:06:47,708
someone else attacked him,
and he died of those injuries.

83
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:50,043
That’s why I came here.

84
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:52,713
I wanted to find out
if there were any intruders.

85
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:55,349
They might be hiding
in the crowd somewhere.

86
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:58,418
( Shaiapouf pants )

87
00:06:58,452 --> 00:07:00,020
Welfin: Eh?

88
00:07:00,053 --> 00:07:01,755
( Groans )

89
00:07:01,788 --> 00:07:05,425
The royal guard pouf.
Oh, he’s trouble.

90
00:07:05,459 --> 00:07:10,030
I’m pretty sure he has
the ability to read my mind.

91
00:07:10,063 --> 00:07:11,798
Shaiapouf: Welfin is
a serious threat

92
00:07:11,832 --> 00:07:13,467
to my carefully laid plans.

93
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:16,136
I have no clue
what he might tell the king.

94
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:19,740
Simply asking him to keep quiet
would be too lenient.

95
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:22,142
I should eliminate him
immediately.

96
00:07:22,176 --> 00:07:26,147
I should accuse him
of disloyalty and execute him.

97
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:30,685
In any case, I must get him
away from the king.

98
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:34,087
Lord meruem, welfin is--

99
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:36,624
meruem: I already know
what you’re about to say.

100
00:07:36,657 --> 00:07:37,758
( Shaiapouf gasps )

101
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,593
Meruem: I can now
sense the emotions

102
00:07:39,626 --> 00:07:41,995
of everyone
whom my en has touched,

103
00:07:42,029 --> 00:07:45,766
and his hostility towards me
is quite extraordinary.

104
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:47,100
( Welfin gasps )

105
00:07:48,202 --> 00:07:51,172
Shaiapouf: That’s incredible.

106
00:07:51,205 --> 00:07:53,107
Meruem: In the exact moment

107
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:55,976
someone has been exposed
to my en,

108
00:07:56,009 --> 00:07:58,678
I become able
to see into their heart.

109
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,016
Shaiapouf: So it wasn’t
just youpi’s wings and attacks.

110
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:06,186
The king also inherited
my spiritual message.

111
00:08:06,220 --> 00:08:08,189
Not only that,

112
00:08:08,222 --> 00:08:11,992
but it seems he’s made it
infinitely more powerful.

113
00:08:12,025 --> 00:08:13,593
( Gasps )

114
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:15,996
Sire!

115
00:08:16,029 --> 00:08:18,598
The king is invincible!

116
00:08:18,632 --> 00:08:20,934
The king is unrivaled!

117
00:08:22,035 --> 00:08:23,904
And yet...

118
00:08:23,937 --> 00:08:25,572
( Heart beating )

119
00:08:26,773 --> 00:08:27,907
Why?!

120
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:33,680
What is this feeling
washing over me?

121
00:08:33,714 --> 00:08:39,420
Why is my heart filled
with such overwhelming anxiety?

122
00:08:40,921 --> 00:08:42,089
Meruem: Now then,

123
00:08:42,122 --> 00:08:45,792
there is a fair amount
of fear mixed in,

124
00:08:45,826 --> 00:08:47,161
but there is no hiding

125
00:08:47,194 --> 00:08:49,730
the raw malice
that you feel for me.

126
00:08:49,763 --> 00:08:51,898
It surges even now.

127
00:08:51,932 --> 00:08:54,968
Your hatred is undeniable,

128
00:08:55,002 --> 00:08:58,639
and I am quite interested
to learn what drives it.

129
00:09:01,742 --> 00:09:07,081
Speak, but lie to me,
and you will regret it.

130
00:09:07,114 --> 00:09:08,916
( Welfin wails )

131
00:09:08,949 --> 00:09:12,052
Shaiapouf: This is no time
to let emotion best me.

132
00:09:13,153 --> 00:09:15,122
Meruem: Tell me what you know.

133
00:09:15,155 --> 00:09:17,024
( Exoskeleton crackles )

134
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:18,058
Shaiapouf: Lord meruem!

135
00:09:21,161 --> 00:09:24,131
Please forgive me
for speaking out of turn.

136
00:09:24,164 --> 00:09:26,066
♪

137
00:09:39,546 --> 00:09:42,883
Shaiapouf: He is
deeply involved in my secret.

138
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:46,119
However, he has
not yet realized this.

139
00:09:46,153 --> 00:09:48,055
Welfin: Huh? Huh?!

140
00:09:49,556 --> 00:09:51,024
Shaiapouf: You may
continue to question him

141
00:09:51,058 --> 00:09:54,228
if you wish, sire.
That is your right, of course.

142
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:55,929
But it is highly likely

143
00:09:55,963 --> 00:10:00,534
he will divulge
some or all of my secret.

144
00:10:00,567 --> 00:10:04,271
When the king has such power,
lies are futile.

145
00:10:04,304 --> 00:10:06,940
I must rely on the truth.

146
00:10:06,974 --> 00:10:10,110
Although I am certain
you wish to receive your reward,

147
00:10:10,143 --> 00:10:12,045
I cannot imagine
you would want it

148
00:10:12,079 --> 00:10:13,948
before winning the contest.

149
00:10:13,981 --> 00:10:17,151
I can use the truth
to muddle the facts.

150
00:10:17,184 --> 00:10:22,189
If you desire,
the game will continue.

151
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:24,958
It is my belief
that you should wait

152
00:10:24,992 --> 00:10:27,161
before you question him further.

153
00:10:27,194 --> 00:10:30,764
Welfin: Hold on. What the hell
is this guy talking about?

154
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:33,867
Secret? What secret?

155
00:10:33,901 --> 00:10:37,138
Wait. What am I
supposed to do now?

156
00:10:37,171 --> 00:10:39,573
How do I escape
from this monster?

157
00:10:39,606 --> 00:10:42,175
What happens next?

158
00:10:42,209 --> 00:10:45,779
Damn it. I didn’t realize
he was this powerful.

159
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:48,315
I should have run away
right off the bat.

160
00:10:48,348 --> 00:10:50,984
( Groans )
Temptation got the better of me.

161
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:53,954
When I saw how youpi
had shrunken from a giant

162
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,957
down to the size of a bug,
then dropped dead,

163
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:59,593
I started thinking
I might be strong enough

164
00:10:59,626 --> 00:11:00,827
to take down the king.

165
00:11:00,861 --> 00:11:03,163
Oh, but that
was just a delusion.

166
00:11:03,197 --> 00:11:04,565
That’s why I stayed.

167
00:11:04,598 --> 00:11:07,034
It was all wishful thinking.

168
00:11:08,368 --> 00:11:09,703
I felt invincible,

169
00:11:09,736 --> 00:11:11,238
like some sheltered child.

170
00:11:11,271 --> 00:11:12,773
I felt alive.

171
00:11:12,806 --> 00:11:14,274
I’m such an idiot.

172
00:11:14,308 --> 00:11:16,877
I was drunk on my own fantasy.

173
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:19,779
In all the chaos that happened,

174
00:11:19,813 --> 00:11:22,582
I remembered gyro
and got caught up

175
00:11:22,616 --> 00:11:25,786
in the delusions
of sentimentality and heroism.

176
00:11:25,819 --> 00:11:29,589
I was sure I could avenge gyro,

177
00:11:29,623 --> 00:11:31,625
but he isn’t even dead.

178
00:11:31,658 --> 00:11:34,194
Gyro’s alive. He has to be.

179
00:11:34,228 --> 00:11:37,665
I should have run off
and teamed up with him again.

180
00:11:37,698 --> 00:11:40,201
Then we could have
sought revenge.

181
00:11:40,234 --> 00:11:44,038
Damn it.
It’s all that octopus’s fault.

182
00:11:44,071 --> 00:11:46,206
That little bastard
threw me off my game.

183
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,709
He messed with my emotions.

184
00:11:48,742 --> 00:11:51,211
I let him lead me astray.

185
00:11:51,245 --> 00:11:53,714
( Groans ) Messenger, my ass.

186
00:11:53,747 --> 00:11:55,949
I have to do something.

187
00:11:55,983 --> 00:11:59,920
He knows my intent is hostile,
and I can’t lie.

188
00:11:59,953 --> 00:12:03,857
He’ll send my head flying before
I can even activate missileman.

189
00:12:05,159 --> 00:12:07,662
Think.
What tools do I have left?

190
00:12:09,696 --> 00:12:12,332
The message? Pouf’s secret?

191
00:12:12,366 --> 00:12:14,101
The root of my hatred?

192
00:12:14,134 --> 00:12:18,639
If I tell him everything I know,
will it be enough to save me?

193
00:12:18,672 --> 00:12:20,174
What do I say?

194
00:12:20,207 --> 00:12:22,242
Whatever it is,

195
00:12:22,276 --> 00:12:25,780
the first word out of my mouth
will be crucial.

196
00:12:25,812 --> 00:12:30,350
Just one word will decide
whether I live or die.

197
00:12:30,384 --> 00:12:34,355
If I choose the wrong one,
it’s all over.

198
00:12:34,388 --> 00:12:36,290
( Aura whooshing )

199
00:12:41,061 --> 00:12:43,030
This overwhelming pressure.

200
00:12:43,063 --> 00:12:45,132
This abnormal tension.

201
00:12:45,165 --> 00:12:49,803
Meruem: Tell me,
does welfin’s malice

202
00:12:49,837 --> 00:12:53,674
have any relationship
to the secret you are keeping?

203
00:12:54,942 --> 00:12:56,143
( Welfin gasps )

204
00:12:56,176 --> 00:12:58,745
Meruem: Think carefully
before you answer.

205
00:12:58,779 --> 00:13:01,081
Welfin: This is the king.

206
00:13:03,183 --> 00:13:07,921
Meruem: You interrupted me and
tried to influence my decision.

207
00:13:07,955 --> 00:13:10,891
That will have consequences.

208
00:13:10,924 --> 00:13:13,760
I must presume that you
are prepared for them.

209
00:13:13,794 --> 00:13:15,162
( Shaiapouf gasping )

210
00:13:15,195 --> 00:13:18,265
Meruem: I want a sincere answer.

211
00:13:18,298 --> 00:13:19,800
Shaiapouf: This is...

212
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:22,769
Narrator: The king’s new power

213
00:13:22,803 --> 00:13:24,972
meant he had access
to the answer.

214
00:13:25,005 --> 00:13:27,107
He could probe
pouf’s mind for it

215
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,075
without waiting
for him to speak.

216
00:13:29,109 --> 00:13:34,247
Although he understood that he
had pouf’s absolute devotion,

217
00:13:34,281 --> 00:13:37,317
the king’s deathly aura
revealed his intent.

218
00:13:37,351 --> 00:13:40,721
In truth, it was unmistakable.

219
00:13:40,754 --> 00:13:43,123
If the answer
did not please the king,

220
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:45,058
whether right or wrong,

221
00:13:45,092 --> 00:13:48,896
pouf would pay the penalty
with his life.

222
00:13:48,929 --> 00:13:51,899
Loyalty, hostility,

223
00:13:51,932 --> 00:13:54,802
each of these factors
were equally meaningless

224
00:13:54,835 --> 00:13:56,370
in the eyes of the king.

225
00:13:57,437 --> 00:14:00,907
No one could stop him.

226
00:14:00,941 --> 00:14:02,876
♪

227
00:14:04,278 --> 00:14:05,479
Shaiapouf: Even then...

228
00:14:07,214 --> 00:14:08,449
I was prepared.

229
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:13,987
I already knew
that I was going to die.

230
00:14:16,490 --> 00:14:21,996
I will sacrifice myself
to my own loyalty.

231
00:14:24,798 --> 00:14:28,902
I-I have no words left to say.

232
00:14:31,004 --> 00:14:32,906
We are in the midst
of our match.

233
00:14:37,211 --> 00:14:40,448
Nothing less, nothing more.

234
00:14:50,357 --> 00:14:54,094
Narrator: His resolve was
nothing short of incredible.

235
00:14:54,127 --> 00:14:57,464
That, as well as his insanity,

236
00:14:57,498 --> 00:15:00,835
stopped the king in his tracks.

237
00:15:10,611 --> 00:15:12,012
Meruem: I am hungry.

238
00:15:14,982 --> 00:15:16,150
Narrator: But...

239
00:15:17,851 --> 00:15:19,486
( Welfin yelps )

240
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:22,156
Narrator: Welfin
understood immediately.

241
00:15:23,924 --> 00:15:26,226
Welfin: This is it.

242
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:29,230
He’s going to eat me.

243
00:15:29,263 --> 00:15:32,032
♪

244
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:34,235
( Heart beating )

245
00:15:34,268 --> 00:15:36,303
Narrator: One second from now...

246
00:15:36,336 --> 00:15:38,238
( Heart beating )

247
00:15:41,475 --> 00:15:42,977
Welfin: I’m dead.

248
00:15:44,578 --> 00:15:48,849
Narrator: Sensing his own fate,
welfin began to age,

249
00:15:48,882 --> 00:15:53,453
and within moments, it was as if
a hundred years had passed.

250
00:15:53,487 --> 00:15:56,056
Welfin: I want to live.

251
00:15:58,625 --> 00:16:00,327
Narrator: In his mind,

252
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:04,164
welfin’s entire life passed
by him in a jumbled flash,

253
00:16:04,198 --> 00:16:08,602
and then it burst, blending
seamlessly with the present.

254
00:16:09,903 --> 00:16:11,204
Welfin: One word...

255
00:16:12,306 --> 00:16:17,878
My first and my last.

256
00:16:17,911 --> 00:16:20,280
Narrator: Caught between
the desire to live

257
00:16:20,314 --> 00:16:22,016
and unavoidable death...

258
00:16:25,352 --> 00:16:26,553
Welfin: One word.

259
00:16:28,121 --> 00:16:29,889
The message for the king.

260
00:16:29,923 --> 00:16:31,892
One word.

261
00:16:31,925 --> 00:16:34,895
What pouf discussed with pitou.

262
00:16:34,928 --> 00:16:36,296
One word.

263
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:38,566
Pouf’s secret.

264
00:16:38,599 --> 00:16:40,101
One word.

265
00:16:40,133 --> 00:16:41,501
I won’t die.

266
00:16:41,535 --> 00:16:43,504
One word.

267
00:16:43,537 --> 00:16:45,906
Don’t die until you’re dead!

268
00:16:45,939 --> 00:16:47,374
( Chorus vocalizing )

269
00:16:47,407 --> 00:16:49,676
Narrator: His brain
worked feverishly

270
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:52,613
as it never had before
and selected a word

271
00:16:52,646 --> 00:16:54,248
that, under normal conditions,

272
00:16:54,281 --> 00:16:56,650
never would have
occurred to him.

273
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:06,627
Welfin: Komugi.

274
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,595
♪

275
00:18:08,789 --> 00:18:12,426
Shaiapouf: This--this is...

276
00:18:17,798 --> 00:18:21,535
This is how intensely
he cares for her.

277
00:18:26,273 --> 00:18:27,241
Meruem: Pouf.

278
00:18:29,076 --> 00:18:31,245
So this is your secret.

279
00:18:32,312 --> 00:18:33,246
Shaiapouf: Yes.

280
00:18:35,349 --> 00:18:38,118
He cares more than I feared.

281
00:18:38,151 --> 00:18:41,655
I will accept any punishment.

282
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:48,529
Meruem: You know
what it shall be.

283
00:18:48,562 --> 00:18:50,697
I do not have to speak it.

284
00:18:50,731 --> 00:18:53,067
You and I are of one mind.

285
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:55,469
I do not blame you.

286
00:18:55,502 --> 00:18:58,038
Shaiapouf: I never had a chance.

287
00:19:00,207 --> 00:19:01,341
Yes.

288
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:03,577
Meruem: Continue
searching for pitou.

289
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:07,547
The two captured intruders
may know something.

290
00:19:07,581 --> 00:19:10,384
Once you are done, let them go.

291
00:19:10,417 --> 00:19:12,753
I have nothing else
to ask of them.

292
00:19:14,555 --> 00:19:18,292
Shaiapouf: All I can do
is nod in assent.

293
00:19:19,359 --> 00:19:20,293
Sire.

294
00:19:21,395 --> 00:19:23,530
Meruem: The opened door,

295
00:19:23,564 --> 00:19:26,600
the footprints leading inside,

296
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:30,303
the resolve of those
I sensed with my en,

297
00:19:30,337 --> 00:19:32,773
all signs lead to one solution.

298
00:19:32,806 --> 00:19:34,708
Welfin.

299
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:38,578
Welfin: Sire, i--what is it?

300
00:19:38,612 --> 00:19:41,615
Meruem: Komugi is
in the underground warehouse

301
00:19:41,648 --> 00:19:44,384
along with the woman
and the octopus.

302
00:19:44,418 --> 00:19:48,188
You were to deliver that
information to me or my guards.

303
00:19:48,222 --> 00:19:50,524
Welfin: But how
did you know that?

304
00:19:50,557 --> 00:19:53,193
Meruem: I have come to believe
that you took on the task

305
00:19:53,227 --> 00:19:55,863
at the behest of the octopus,

306
00:19:55,896 --> 00:19:59,800
but I am unsure
why you failed to carry it out.

307
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:03,303
Is it connected to your deep
and sudden hatred of me,

308
00:20:03,337 --> 00:20:04,305
by any chance?

309
00:20:04,338 --> 00:20:06,574
( Welfin gasps )

310
00:20:06,607 --> 00:20:07,708
Meruem: Ah, yes.

311
00:20:07,741 --> 00:20:10,310
Now please be at ease.

312
00:20:10,344 --> 00:20:11,712
Just answer my question,

313
00:20:11,745 --> 00:20:13,847
and you are free to go
wherever you wish.

314
00:20:15,916 --> 00:20:18,152
You have my thanks.

315
00:20:18,185 --> 00:20:19,653
It’s because of you

316
00:20:19,686 --> 00:20:21,655
that I remembered
something important.

317
00:20:23,323 --> 00:20:24,257
( Welfin grumbles )

318
00:20:26,360 --> 00:20:31,432
Area d. They said they’d wait
in bizeff’s courtyard.

319
00:20:31,465 --> 00:20:34,435
( Gasping )

320
00:20:34,468 --> 00:20:37,237
( Growls )

321
00:20:37,271 --> 00:20:40,808
Gyro is the only man
I will ever call king!

322
00:20:40,841 --> 00:20:44,745
You, all of you, you’re enemies!

323
00:20:44,778 --> 00:20:46,546
Do you hear me?!

324
00:20:48,649 --> 00:20:49,850
Meruem: Is that so?

325
00:20:49,883 --> 00:20:52,853
( Welfin panting )

326
00:20:52,886 --> 00:20:56,857
Meruem: I hope you see him.
I truly do.

327
00:20:56,890 --> 00:20:59,393
And, if possible...

328
00:21:00,494 --> 00:21:03,664
Go live a human life.

329
00:21:03,697 --> 00:21:05,799
( Shaiapouf wails )

330
00:21:12,506 --> 00:21:14,475
♪

331
00:21:14,508 --> 00:21:15,876
Narrator: Netero once believed

332
00:21:15,909 --> 00:21:19,179
that the king was wavering
on the brink that lies

333
00:21:19,213 --> 00:21:23,617
between the human world and
that of the ants, but now...

334
00:21:25,452 --> 00:21:27,387
( Singing in Japanese )

